git commit -m "feat: implement responsive park website with modern frontend stack

Frontend Architecture:
- Semantic HTML5 structure with accessibility considerations
- CSS3 with CSS Grid & Flexbox layouts
- Mobile-first responsive design approach
- CSS custom properties (variables) for theming

JavaScript Features:
- DOM manipulation for interactive components
- Event delegation for dynamic elements
- Scroll-based animations using Intersection Observer pattern
- Modal system with backdrop click handling
- Form validation and dynamic pricing calculation

Performance Optimizations:
- Optimized images with responsive sizing
- Efficient CSS selectors and minimal reflows
- Debounced scroll events
- Lazy loading potential for gallery images

Technical Implementation Details:
- Responsive navigation with hamburger menu (max-width: 968px breakpoint)
- Hero section with gradient overlay and background-attachment
- About section with scroll-triggered fade animations
- Gallery grid using CSS Grid with auto-fill pattern
- Ticket booking system with real-time price updates
- Contact form with proper input types
- Cross-browser compatible CSS transitions
- CSS BEM-like naming convention for components

Code Structure:
- Modular CSS organization by component
- Separation of concerns (HTML structure, CSS styling, JS behavior)
- Reusable utility classes and components
- Clean, commented code for maintainability"

